forest.tooltip:
Forests are the most common surface biomes, and are where the player usually spawns upon starting a new world.

Green grass grows across the dirt, which can spawn {{Mushrooms}}, {{Dayblooms}}, and trees. Forests appear whenever no other biome is valid.

{{@image forest_biome_banner}}

snow_biome.tooltip:
The Snow biome is a winter-themed biome predominately made of {{Snow Block}} and {{Ice Block}}.

The Snow biome is always located on the same side as the {{Dungeon}} and on the opposite side of the {{Jungle}}.

{{@image snow_biome_banner}}

desert.tooltip:
Deserts are large expanses of {{Sand}}.

Their vegetation is comparatively sparse, consisting solely of {{Cactus}}.

{{@image desert_biome_banner}}

corruption.tooltip:
The Corruption follows a rotten theme and features vertical chasms, {{Shadow Orb}}, and {{Demon Altar}}.

A world will always generate with an evil biome – either {{Crimson}} or {{Corruption}}, but never both.

{{@image the_corruption_biome_banner}}

crimson.tooltip:
The Crimson follows a gory theme and features angled passages, {{Crimson Heart}}, and {{Crimson Altar}}.

A world will always generate with an evil biome – either {{Crimson}} or {{Corruption}}, but never both.

{{@image the_crimson_biome_banner}}

jungle.tooltip:
A surface biome composed primarily of grass, vines, mud, jungle trees, bamboo and pools of water.

The Jungle is always located on the opposite side of the {{Snow biome}} and the {{Dungeon}}, and the same side as the {{Underground Desert}}.

{{@image jungle_biome_banner}}

dungeon.tooltip:
The Dungeon is a labyrinth leading from the {{Surface}} down to near-{{Underworld}} depths.

The {{Old Man}} stands at the entrance, and using him to defeat {{Skeletron}} is required to gain access to the inside.

{{@image dungeon_biome_banner}}

ocean.tooltip:
A biome found at both left and right edges of a world.

{{Duke Fishron}} can be summoned here with a {{Truffle Worm}}. The {{Magic Conch}} can be used to teleport the player to an Ocean.

{{@image ocean_biome_banner}}

ice_biome.tooltip:
The Ice biome is the more dangerous part of the {{Snow biome}} within the {{Cavern}} layer, located beneath the {{Surface}}. Thin Ice layers cover ledges and water, which can break if landed on with high speed.

{{Frozen Chest}} here contain ice-themed equipment.

{{@image ice_biome_banner}}

underground_desert.tooltip:
The Underground Desert is located beneath the surface {{Desert}}.

The biome always has either a circular or an oval shape and contains various types of {{Antlion}} as well as Hardmode enemies themed after ancient Egypt.

{{@image underground_desert_biome_banner}}

underground_jungle.tooltip:
The Underground Jungle is located beneath the surface {{Jungle}}.

Its dense catacomb of compartments contain several hazards and dense vegetation. In Hardmode, the valuable {{Chlorophyte Ore}} can be mined here.

{{@image underground_jungle_biome_banner}}

glowing_mushroom_biome.tooltip:
A biome characterized by Mushroom grass, {{Glowing Mushroom}}, and {{Giant Glowing Mushroom}} growing on Mud Blocks.

It is the only place where {{Truffle Worm}} can be obtained.

{{@image glowing_mushroom_biome_banner}}

the_hallow.tooltip:
The Hallow can be considered the counterpart to the evil biome.

It is automatically created once the player activates Hardmode by defeating the {{Wall of Flesh}}, and has pastel-colored fairy-tale imagery.

{{@image the_hallow_biome_banner}}

underground_hallow.tooltip:
The Underground Hallow is located beneath {{the Hallow}}, starting at the {{Cavern}} layer.

It contains valuable items, such as {{Soul of Light}} and {{Crystal Shard}}.

{{@image underground_hallow_biome_banner}}

underground_corruption.tooltip:
Either The {{Underground Corruption}} or {{Underground Crimson}} is created in the {{Cavern}} layer upon defeating the {{Wall of Flesh}}.

It is the only place where enemies drop {{Cursed Flames}}. These are the only places to obtain {{Souls of Night}}, which are occasionally dropped by all enemies.

{{@image underground_corruption_biome_banner}}

underground_crimson.tooltip:
Either The {{Underground Corruption}} or {{Underground Crimson}} is created in the {{Cavern}} layer upon defeating the {{Wall of Flesh}}.

It is the only place where enemies drop {{Cursed Flames}}. These are the only places to obtain {{Souls of Night}}, which are occasionally dropped by all enemies.

{{@image underground_crimson_biome_banner}}

slime_rain.tooltip:
Slime Rain is a minor event that consists of frequent spawns of {{Green Slime}}, {{Blue Slime}}, and {{Purple Slime}}, and rarely {{Pinky}}.

It occurs randomly, signaling its beginning with the status message "Slime is falling from the sky!".

{{@image slime_rain_banner}}

bee_hive_biome_.tooltip:
A {{Mini-biome}} located in the {{Underground Jungle}}.

The hive itself is made from {{Hive}} blocks; on the interior, it contains pools of {{Honey}} and typically one {{Larva}}.

{{@image bee_hive_biome_banner}}

jungle_temple.tooltip:
An enclosed structure constructed of {{Lihzahrd Brick}} and located in the {{Underground Jungle}}.

It is always present in any generated world. The door is initially locked, requiring a {{Temple Key}} to open, which is dropped by {{Plantera}}.

{{@image jungle_temple_biome_banner}}

pirate_invasion.tooltip:
A Hardmode event where pirate enemies swarm the world's original spawn point.

It triggers randomly or by using {{Pirate Map}}.

{{@image pirate_invasion_banner}}

pumpkin_moon.tooltip:
A {{Hardmode}}, post-{{Plantera}}, Halloween-themed event summoned with the {{Pumpkin Moon Medallion}} any time at night, ending at dawn (4:30 AM).

It can be summoned any time of year and does not require the actual Halloween season.

{{@image pumpkin_moon_banner}}

frost_moon.tooltip:
A {{Hardmode}}, post-{{Plantera}}, Christmas-themed event summoned with {{Naughty Present}} any time at night, ending at dawn (4:30 AM).

It can be summoned any time of year and does not require the actual Christmas season.

{{@image frost_moon_banner}}

solar_eclipse.tooltip:
An event that occurs after defeating one of the {{Mechanical Bosses}}, with a {{@class=primary 5%}} chance at dawn, lasting until sunset.

It can also be manually triggered using a {{Solar Tablet}}. Unique drops:

Weapons: {{Death Sickle}} {{Toxic Flask}} {{The Eye of Cthulhu}} {{Deadly Sphere Staff}} {{Butcher's Chainsaw}} {{Nail Gun}} {{Psycho Knife}}

Accessories: {{Mothron Wings}} {{Moon Stone}} {{Neptune's Shell}} {{Eye Spring}}

Other: {{Broken Hero Sword}} {{Butcher's Set}} {{Dr. Man Fly Set}} {{Steak}} {{Broken Bat Wing}}

{{@image solar_eclipse_banner}}
